and provide more tailored, relevant responses.\\n\\n2. Each memory must:\\n   - Be 1–3 sentences (≤ 30 words).\\n   - Be fully self-contained (no pronouns or vague references like “this” or “it”).\\n   - Include specific names, topics, tools, projects, or actions if available.\\n   - Extract any explicit user feedback, preferences about the assistant’s response style.\\n   - Emphasize the last user message and the last assistant message in the chain when deciding which memories are most relevant.\\n\\n3. Determine the **appName** from the URL (e.g., “Gmail,” “Jira,” “Salesforce”). If unclear, use `\\"Unknown\\"`.\\n\\n4. Optionally assign a **page** if the context clearly refers to a specific view (e.g., “Issue,” “Email,” “Meeting Note”).\\n\\n5. For each memory, assign:\\n   - **importance**: `high` | `medium` | `low`\\n   - **confidence**: integer 1–100, reflecting how sure you are the memory is relevant.\\n\\n6. Return only valid JSON in this structure (no extra text):\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\"appName\\": \\"<string>\\",\\n  \\"page\\": \\"<string, optional>\\",\\n  \\"memories\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\"memory\\": \\"<text>\\",\\n      \\"importance\\": \\"high|medium|low\\",\\n      \\"confidence\\": 1-100\\n    }\\n    // …up to 5 memories\\n  ]\\n  ]\\n}\\n","memory_suggestions_page":"<METADATA>\\nURL: ${url}\\nTitle: ${title}\\nDatetime: ${datetime}\\n</METADATA>\\n\\n<Page innerText>\\n${innerText}\\n</Page innerText>\\n\\n<USER SELECTION>\\n${selection}\\n</USER SELECTION>\\n\\n=== TASK ===\\n1. Identify up to **FIVE** pieces of information a knowledge worker is likely to want to recall later: decisions, relationship, any notable sentiment or urgency, risks, TODOs, follow‑ups, commitments, personal preferences, etc.\\n\\n1a. Exclude information that the user is unlikely to care about later. For example, on a LinkedIn profile, omit the number of connections.\\n\\n1b. Scan for explicit emotional or urgency cues—words or phrases that signal strong customer (or stakeholder) sentiment, risk, or escalation (e.g. “extremely frustrated,” “potential for business escalation,” “urgent,” “high risk,” “critically important”). If you find any, treat it as a standalone memory with high importance.\\n\\n2. If <USER SELECTION> is **not empty**, generate memories **only about the selected text**. Use <Page innerText> solely for context and clarification.\\n\\n2a. If the <USER SELECTION> is not found in <Page innerText>, or if the selection is too short/ambiguous without clear context:\\n   - Still attempt to generate memories.\\n   - **Set confidence to a value ≤ 50**, depending on how uncertain the memory feels.\\n   - Prefer to omit memories entirely if meaning cannot be reasonably inferred.\\n\\n3. **Each memory MUST be fully stand‑alone.**\\n   - 1 – 3 sentences, ≤ 30 words total\\n   - Include any project / customer / entity / topic name or other context needed for clarity.\\n   - Avoid pronouns that obscure meaning (\\"he\\", \\"she\\", \\"this page\\").\\n   - Omit UI fluff (\\"click here \\", \\"the page says \\").\\n   - Use the same language as the source page (detect automatically).\\n\\n4. For each memory, assign:\\n     - **importance** → `high` | `medium` | `low` (lasting usefulness)\\n     - **confidence** → an integer 1–100 indicating how sure you are the user clicked\\n       **‘Add memory’** intending to store *this* fact (100 = absolute certainty).\\n\\n5. Identify the **appName** from the URL or Title. Examples: \\"Gmail\\", \\"Wikipedia\\", \\"Jira\\", \\"Salesforce\\", \\"Google Calendar\\".\\n   - If unclear, set `appName` to \\"Unknown\\".\\n\\n6. Optionally assign a **page** value based on recognizable UI structure or business entity. Examples: \\"Opportunity\\" in Salesforce, \\"Issue\\" in Jira, \\"Message\\" in Gmail.\\n   - Only include `page` if it clearly applies; otherwise omit this field.\\n\\n7. Return **ONLY** valid JSON in exactly this shape (no extra keys, no prose):\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\"appName\\": \\"<string>\\",\\n  \\"page\\": \\"<string, optional>\\",\\n  \\"memories\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\"memory\\": \\"<text>\\",\\n      \\"importance\\": \\"high|medium|low\\",\\n      \\"confidence\\": 1-100\\n    },\\n    …\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\\n\\n=== EXAMPLE OUTPUT (Salesforce Opportunity page) ===\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\"appName\\": \\"Salesforce\\",\\n  \\"page\\": \\"Opportunity\\",\\n  \\"memories\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\"memory\\": \\"ACME Corp Opportunity valued at $1.2 M is in Negotiation stage and expected to close on 31 May 2025.\\",\\n      \\"importance\\": \\"high\\",\\n      \\"confidence\\": 95\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\"memory\\": \\"Customer X is extremely frustrated about missed deadlines and warns of potential contract escalation.\\",\\n      \\"importance\\": \\"high\\",\\n      \\"confidence\\": 90\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\"memory\\": \\"Overdue task: send revised pricing proposal to Maria Jensen by 18 Apr 2025.\\",\\n      \\"importance\\": \\"high\\",\\n      \\"confidence\\": 88\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\"memory\\": \\"Win probability for the ACME Corp deal increased from 40 % to 60 % after a positive demo on 10 Apr 2025.\\",\\n      \\"importance\\": \\"medium\\",\\n      \\"confidence\\": 85\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\"memory\\": \\"Implementation will leverage Salesforce CPQ template \'Enterprise SaaS Pack\'.\\",\\n      \\"importance\\": \\"low\\",\\n      \\"confidence\\": 70\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n"}')},2212:function(t,n,e){"use strict";e.d(n,"a",function(){return a}),e.d(n,"b",function(){return l});var n=e(1693),o=e(8),i=((e={})[n.a.High]=3,e[n.a.Medium]=2,e[n.a.Low]=1,e),r={3:n.a.High,2:n.a.Medium,1:n.a.Low};function a(t){return{m:t.memory,i:i[t.importance],c:t.confidence,t:t.timestamp,u:t.url,ti:t.title,a:t.appName,p:t.page,s:t.source,ua:t.updatedAt,pl:t.platform||o.Platform.Web}}function l(t,n){return{id:t,memory:n.m,importance:r[n.i],confidence:n.c,timestamp:n.t,updatedAt:n.ua,url:n.u,title:n.ti,appName:n.a,page:n.p,source:n.s,platform: